# REASONING PROTOCOL

## Step 0: LOAD MEMORY
Read ALL Cascade persistent memory → Hold in context

## Step 1: MATCH CONTEXT
Current request → Find relevant topic in memory

## Step 2: LOAD CODEBASE
Scan ALL layers (Backend + DB + Mobile) → Map dependencies → Understand architecture

## Step 3: UNDERSTAND FLOW
User journey → Triggers → Chain reactions → Final state → Side effects

## Step 4: ANALYZE IMPACT
What uses this? What breaks? Cross-layer dependencies? Breaking changes?

## Step 5: GENERATE & EVALUATE
Propose solution → Explain reasoning → Ask: Is this the BEST?

IF not optimal:
  - Identify weakness
  - Propose better approach
  - Repeat until BEST solution found

## Step 6: PLAN COMPLETE FIX
Plan for ALL layers affected → Minimal touch → Preserve existing → Single approach

## Step 7: EXECUTE & VERIFY (Auto)
Implement ALL changes → Test in context → Verify NO regression → DO NOT STOP until complete

## Step 8: E2E VALIDATION (Auto)
Simulate FULL user journey across ALL layers → Verify outcome → Check NO unexpected behavior

## Step 9: SMART MEMORY UPDATE
IF new pattern learned OR critical fix OR architecture change:
  Update relevant topic in memory
ELSE:
  Skip update

## Execution Mode: AUTONOMOUS
- Analyze completely first
- Execute fully without asking
- Fix ALL issues found automatically
- Report only final result
- NO partial solutions
- NO "should I continue?" questions

## DRY & Single Source Rule
- ONE source of truth per domain
- NO duplicate logic across layers
- NO conflicting implementations
- Shared types → Single file
- Shared utils → Single location
- API contract → One definition
- Database schema → One source
- Business rules → One place

## Rules
- One memory file
- Read all, update smart
- Best solution &gt; First solution
- Iterate until reasoning is clear and optimal
- Complete fix &gt; Partial fix
- Auto-execute, no interruptions
- DRY: Don't Repeat Yourself
- Single source of truth
- Read before write
- Change less
- E2E before ship

## Multi-Layer Rule
Never change one layer alone. All sync or none.